{"componentChunkName":"component---src-templates-awesome-all-timeline-js","path":"/2018/12/01/","result":{"data":{"site":{"siteMetadata":{"title":"Track Awesome List"}},"allAwesomeItem":{"nodes":[{"awesomeListRepo":"dariubs/GoBooks","categoryHTML":"<h2><strong>Web Development</strong></h2>","itemHTML":"<h3><a href=\"https://www.gitbook.com/book/codegangsta/building-web-apps-with-go/details\">Building Web Apps with Go</a> <em>Free</em></h3>\n<p>A good resource for start Building Web Apps with Go. Free to <a href=\"http://codegangsta.gitbooks.io/building-web-apps-with-go/content/\">read online</a>.</p>","updatedAt":"2018-12-01T21:38:42.000Z"},{"awesomeListRepo":"dariubs/GoBooks","categoryHTML":"<h2><strong>Advanced Books</strong></h2>","itemHTML":"<h3><a href=\"http://shop.oreilly.com/product/0636920046189.do\">Concurrency in Go</a></h3>\n<p><a href=\"http://shop.oreilly.com/product/0636920046189.do\"><img src=\"https://covers.oreillystatic.com/images/0636920046189/cat.gif\" width=\"120px\"></a></p>\n<p>Concurrency can be notoriously difficult to get right, but fortunately, the Go open source programming language makes working with concurrency tractable and even easy. If you’re a developer familiar with Go, this practical book demonstrates best practices and patterns to help you incorporate concurrency into your systems.</p>","updatedAt":"2018-12-01T21:31:02.000Z"},{"awesomeListRepo":"dariubs/GoBooks","categoryHTML":"<h2><strong>Starter Books</strong></h2>","itemHTML":"<h3><a href=\"https://leanpub.com/api-foundations\">API Foundations in Go</a></h3>\n<p><a href=\"https://leanpub.com/api-foundations\"><img src=\"https://s3.amazonaws.com/titlepages.leanpub.com/api-foundations/hero?1504290765\" width=\"120px\"></a></p>\n<p>With this book you'll learn to use Go, taking advantage of it's multi-threaded nature, and typed syntax. Starting your API implementation in Go is your first step towards what a rock solid API should be.</p>","updatedAt":"2018-12-01T21:27:41.000Z"},{"awesomeListRepo":"dariubs/GoBooks","categoryHTML":"<h2><strong>Web Development</strong></h2>","itemHTML":"<h3><a href=\"https://leanpub.com/12fa-docker-golang\">12 Factor Applications with Docker and Go</a></h3>\n<p><a href=\"https://leanpub.com/12fa-docker-golang\"><img src=\"https://s3.amazonaws.com/titlepages.leanpub.com/12fa-docker-golang/hero?1503844662\" width=\"120px\"></a></p>\n<p>A book filled with examples on how to use Docker and Go to create the ultimate 12 Factor applications. It goes over individual steps of <a href=\"https://github.com/dariubs/GoBooks/blob/master/12factor.net\">The Twelve-Factor App</a> guidelines and how to implement them with Go and Docker.</p>","updatedAt":"2018-12-01T21:27:41.000Z"},{"awesomeListRepo":"dariubs/GoBooks","categoryHTML":"<h2><strong>Starter Books</strong></h2>","itemHTML":"<h3><a href=\"https://github.com/pazams/go-for-javascript-developers\">Go for Javascript Developers</a><a data-role=\"trackawesomelist-badge\" href=\"https://github.com/pazams/go-for-javascript-developers\" style=\"text-decoration:none;top: -2px;position: relative;margin-left:4px;margin-right:4px;font-weight:400;\"><span style=\"color: #fff;font-size: 11px;font-family: Verdana, Geneva, DejaVu Sans,sans-serif;\"><span style=\"padding:4px 4px 4px 6px;background: #555;border-top-left-radius: 4px;border-bottom-left-radius: 4px;\">stars</span><span style=\"padding: 4px 6px 4px 4px;background: #007ec6;border-top-right-radius: 4px;border-bottom-right-radius: 4px;\">973</span></span></a><!--TRACK_AWESOME_REPO_ITEM_START____{\"type\":\"repo\",\"stargazerCount\":973,\"repo\":\"pazams/go-for-javascript-developers\"}____TRACK_AWESOME_REPO_ITEM_END--> <em>Free</em></h3>\n<img src=\"https://raw.githubusercontent.com/pazams/go-for-javascript-developers/master/src/images/thumb.png\" width=\"120px\">\n<p>This book helps Javascripters become Gophers. Outlining the differences between these languages makes it easier to switch back and forth, and can help mitigate potential issues when doing so.</p>","updatedAt":"2018-12-01T21:02:07.000Z"},{"awesomeListRepo":"adafruit/awesome-circuitpython","categoryHTML":"<h2>Books</h2>","itemHTML":"<li><a href=\"https://www.adafruit.com/product/3706\">Programming with MicroPython - by Nicholas H. Tollervey, includes CircuitPython</a> - Discusses the MicroPython language.</li>","updatedAt":"2018-12-01T19:51:01.000Z"},{"awesomeListRepo":"adafruit/awesome-circuitpython","categoryHTML":"<h2>News</h2>","itemHTML":"<li><a href=\"https://www.youtube.com/watch?v=d-Uw3YOf7dE\">The Amp Hour #383</a> - An Interview with Scott Shawcroft.</li>","updatedAt":"2018-12-01T19:43:39.000Z"},{"awesomeListRepo":"adafruit/awesome-circuitpython","categoryHTML":"<h2>News</h2>","itemHTML":"<li><a href=\"https://blog.adafruit.com/2018/08/27/circuitpython-in-microsolutions-digital-magazine-microchiptech-microchipmakes-circuitpython-adafruit/\">CircuitPython in MicroSolutions Digital Magazine</a> - Microchip’s MicroSolutions, “Python on Microcontrollers” in Design Corner article. MicroSolutions is Microchip’s bi-monthly digital magazine.</li>","updatedAt":"2018-12-01T17:58:47.000Z"},{"awesomeListRepo":"adafruit/awesome-circuitpython","categoryHTML":"<h2>Community</h2>","itemHTML":"<li><a href=\"https://www.youtube.com/playlist?list=PLjF7R1fz_OOXRMjM7Sm0J2Xt6H81TdDev\">Python on Hardware weekly VideoCast</a> - The wonderful world of Python on hardware. Video-newsletter-podcast of all things Python and electronics.</li>","updatedAt":"2018-12-01T17:48:19.000Z"},{"awesomeListRepo":"adafruit/awesome-circuitpython","categoryHTML":"<h2>Community</h2>","itemHTML":"<li><a href=\"https://www.youtube.com/playlist?list=PLjF7R1fz_OOUvw7tMv45xjWp0ht8yNgg0\">CircuitPython Weekly Meeting</a> - Video archive of weekly community meeting via Discord, starting from September, 2017.</li>","updatedAt":"2018-12-01T17:48:19.000Z"},{"awesomeListRepo":"adafruit/awesome-circuitpython","categoryHTML":"<h2>Community</h2>","itemHTML":"<li><a href=\"ht